"'''Day of the Sepulchral Night'''" is a short story written by [[Jean Rabe]] (with illustrations by [[Matt Busch]]), originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 13]] by [[West End Games]] in [[May]] [[1997]], and has since released in the short story anthology ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]] and was later archived online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[February 11]] [[2004]].

==Plot summary==
While on vacation on [[Zelos II]], the [[Weequay/Legends|Weequay]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Diergu-Rea Duhnes'rd]] and his mate [[Solum'ke]] join a [[Treasure hunting/Legends|treasure hunt]] with the [[Qwohog (species)|Qwohog]] [[K'zk]]. Local legend told of sunken treasure in [[Zelosian's Chine]], a prominent coral ridge in the [[Great Zelosi Sea]]. On the [[Day of the Sepulchral Night|Day of the Sepulchral Night]], the fourth [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of Zelos II aligned with the [[Star/Legends|sun]], putting the tides in that region at their lowest and the purported treasure at its most accessible.

The local [[Zelosian|Zelosians]] were very superstitious about the [[Eclipse/Legends|eclipse]] and kept themselves indoors during the Day of the Sepulchral Night. As a Qwohog, K'zk couldn't risk exposure to [[Water/Legends|seawater]], so he offered a 50/50 split with Diergu-Rea and Solum'ke.

On the way to [[Zelosian's Chine]], they encounter two [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] survivors of a recent shipwreck, [[Hanugar]] and [[Sevik (criminal)|Sevik]]. K'zk and the Weequay rescue the survivors and bring them along to Zelosian's Chine. When they reach their destination, Diergu-Rea, Solum'ke and [[Sevik (criminal)|Sevik]] enter a small [[Cave/Legends|cave]], discovering a wealth of [[Crystal/Legends|crystals]] and jewels. The treasure is enough to set all of them for life.

The small cave suddenly begins to fill with water, as the eclipse begins to end. Diergu-Rea and Solum'ke make their way to the surface, only to discover Sevik already boarding the [[Starship/Legends|ship]] with the aid of a [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] belt. Sevik, [[Hanugar]] and K'zk had been collaborating all along. Diergu-Rea and Solum'ke are left stranded on top of Zelosian's Chine.

Solum'ke is upset that they lost everything. However, Diergu-Rea points out that Solum'ke is wearing a green crystal [[Necklace/Legends|necklace]] that he put on her while in the cave, and that his pockets are full of crystals and jewels. Diergu-Rea assures her that another ship will be coming by shortly and tracking down two Corellians and a Qwohog shouldn't be too hard for the best bounty hunters in the sector.

